notices.title: State Dance Company
notices.content: The State Dance Company is an advanced program for talented NSW public school dancers in Years 4‚Äì12. It offers a progression pathway for high-potential dancers through four intensive workshops in Sydney, where students train, rehearse, and perform new works with industry tutors. The program focuses on excellence in technique, composition, and performance, with opportunities to perform at the State Dance Festival and Schools Spectacular.¬†If you are interested in applying, please see Miss McMillan in Staffroom 2 for more information.¬†Applications Close Friday 3rd April (Week 10)
notices.contentHtml:
The State Dance Company is an advanced program for talented NSW public school dancers in Years 4‚Äì12. It offers a progression pathway for high-potential dancers through four intensive workshops in Sydney, where students train, rehearse, and perform new works with industry tutors. The program focuses on excellence in technique, composition, and performance, with opportunities to perform at the State Dance Festival and Schools Spectacular.

 

If you are interested in applying, please see Miss McMillan in Staffroom 2 for more information. 

Applications Close Friday 3rd April (Week 10)
